Testing:
    - As a Angular Developer we can write the Test Cases for Angular Applications.

    - "Karma with Jasmine" is the Automation tool used to write the test cases for UI Applications.

        Ex.
            AngularJS
            Angular2 / Angular4
            reactJS
            NodeJS
                --
                --
                --


Installation of Karma Automation Tool:
--------------------------------------
> npm install -g karma-cli




We Can Categorize the Testing in two types:
-------------------------------------------

1. Manual Testing

2. Automation Testing

Automation Testing Classify into 3 categories.

1. Unit Testing

2. Integration Testing

3. End To End Testing


Unit Testing:
-------------
    - Testing the Perticular Functionality with Dummy Scenarioes called as Unit Testing.

Integration Testing:
--------------------
    - Checking the Perticular Functionality "with presence of project Integration" Called as
      Integration Testing.

End to End Testing:
-------------------
    - Checking the whole application with different scenarioes called as e2e testing


Ex_1:
    Testing Controllers
    -------------------
var app = angular.module("app",[]);

app.controller("ctrl"ctrl);
function ctrl($scope){
    $scope.var_one = "Testing Controller !";
}

//define test suite
describe("first test case",function(){

    //All Controllers Availability.
    var $controller;

    //making the availability of "app" to Test Suite
    module("app");

    //Making the Availability Of Controllers.
    inject(function(_$controller_){
        $controller = _$controller_;
    });
});

it("should return 'Testing Controller !'",function(){
    var result = $controller("ctrl",{$scope});
    expect(result).equalsTo('Testing Controller !');
});


start the test cases(Execute the Test Cases):
---------------------------------------------

> start karma


{{var_one}} //Testing Controller !


Testing the Services:
---------------------
var app = angular.module("app",[]);
app.factory("my_service",my_service);
function my_service(){
    return ["AngularJS",
            "Angular4",
            "reactJS",
            "NodeJS",
            "MongoDB"];
}



describe("testing of service",function(){
    var testService;
    module("app");
    inject(function($injector){
        testService = $injector.get("my_service");
    });
});


it("unit testing",function(){
    var result = testService;
    expect(result).contains("AngularJS");
    expect(result).contains("Angular4");
    expect(result).contains("reactJS");
    expect(result).contains("NodeJS");
    expect(result).contains("MongoDB");
    expect(result).equalsTo(5);

});





